{
  "text": "Also, one can keep in mind that from the LV function perspective, LV GLS has been reported to be an independent prognostic marker in patients with persistent AF referred for echocardiography. In this study, GLS was a major parameter and stronger predictor of adverse cardiovascular events than LVEF or pulsed tissue Doppler. [CITATION_1] Key point 8 (1) The LA lateral wall strain can be reliably imaged and is not constrained by other cardiac chambers and may be used as the best surrogate of LA wall fibrosis by CMR. (2) A LA strain (in systole) ,30% indicates significant alteration of LA reservoir function, which predicts the poor outcome.",
